Calculations are done for samples at 25°C / 77°F. Accuracy is +- 10%.

Active chlorine is the amount of free chlorine in your sample which is not bound to cyanuric acid and thus is actively killing bacteria and algae. Recommended values range from 0.05 to 3.0 ppm, depending on your pool type and location.
This process can take up to 10 minutes, please be patient. Do not close the App and do not lock your phones screen until the process is complete.

<b>Langelier Saturation Index (LSI)</b><br>The LSI is used to determine the scaling potential of a liquid solution. Mostly used for the water of pools and spas to determine if the water has a tendency to form scales (indicated by a positive LSI greater than 0.3) or is corrosive (indicated by a negative LSI lower than -0.3). Thus, a balanced pool or spa should have an LSI between <b>-0.3 and 0.3</b> to neither form scales nor cause corrosion on the equipment.<br><br><b>Ryznar Stability Index (RSI)</b><br>The RSI is also used to give an indication of the calcium carbonate stability of a liquid solution; it indicates whether the solution will precipitate, dissolve, or be in equilibrium with calcium carbonate. It is considered an improvement to the LSI in terms of accuracy. Some also consider the LSI always being a positive number an advantage over the RSI.<br><br>Usual reference values for the <b>RSI</b> are listed below:<br><b>RSI below 5.5:</b> heavy scaling tendency<br><b>RSI between 5.5 and 6.2:</b> scaling tendency<br><b>RSI between 6.2 and 6.9:</b> balanced water<br><b>RSI above 6.9</b> water is corrosive/aggressive

Export the current database as SQLite file. This export includes all accounts, measurements, custom water treatment products and application settings. If you are using the free Cloud Service, please note that your password will NOT be exported and must be re-entered upon database import.

Import the database from a previous file-backup. Note that the currently active database, including all accounts, measurements, custom water treatment products, all application settings as well as cloud logins are discarded. This cannot be undone, so it is recommended to do a backup of the currently active database before importing another.
To merge your current database with an exported one, register on our free Cloud Service to first synchronize your current database to the cloud, then import the file-backup, and finally log-in to your just registered cloud-account with the merge option active.
